Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of two (2) years.  That is one (1) year initial confinement followed by one (1) year extended supervision.
The defendant is found eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) No contact with any known drug dealers or users;
5) Pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) maintain fulltime employment/schooling/work search/combination;
8) maintain absolute sobriety.
The defendant has credit for 224 days.
